    <section class="section pt-5" id="ecommerce_background">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-lg-6 offset-lg-3 col-md-8 offset-md-2">
                    <h3 class="mt-50 mb-30" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="1500" data-aos-easing="ease">Sales dwindling</h3>
                    <p data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="1500" data-aos-easing="ease">Bare Kollections sells eco-friendly, USA made products inspired by minimalist design. The shoppers can now only buy their scented candles on Amazon.</p>
                    <p data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="1500" data-aos-easing="ease">Their Web site was never fully equipped to handle all facets of shopping experience, and it is getting harder for micro businesses, like Bare Kollections to compete with large enterprises on Amazon. On top of that, suppliers don’t
                        seem to value micro businesses and one woman enterprises.</p>
                    <h3 class="mb-30" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="1500" data-aos-easing="ease">Suppliers failing</h3>
                    <p data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="1500" data-aos-easing="ease">That was particularly obvious after several suppliers failed to make their scented candles according to specifications, causing the business to lose customers and money. It was particularly embarrassing when unsatisfied customers left
                        bad reviews on Amazon for the first time, complaining that one of the scented candles smells like Dove soap, although it was supposed to be a mixture scent of sweet mint, basil and lime.</p>
                    <h3 class="mb-30" data-aos="fade-up"
                        data-aos-duration="1500" data-aos-easing="ease">Owner taking action</h3>
                    <p data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="1500" data-aos-easing="ease">The owner decided to take matters into her own hands and come up with a plan to make her business venture more stable and reliable. She is testing new suppliers, and developing new scents for candles and making plans to expand the
                        product line.</p>
                    <p data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="1500" data-aos-easing="ease">In addition, she hired a designer to develop a new e-commerce Web site that will take into account all the business and customer needs.</p>
                    <p data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="1500" data-aos-easing="ease">The new Web site should incorporate all the sales channels such as Amazon and Instagram. It should accommodate customers no matter how they end up on the Web site. It should also enable the owner to easily update the site, add new
                        products, and handle the re-stocking process.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
