    <section class="section bg-how" id="ecommerce_how_research_methods">
        <h3 class="text-center mt-20 mb-50 text-boja" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="1500" data-aos-easing="ease">How</h3>
        <div class="container mb-100">
            <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-8 offset-md-2 col-lg-6 offset-lg-3">
                <div class="accordion" id="accordionExample" data-aos="zoom-in" data-aos-duration="3000" data-aos-easing="ease-in-out-cubic" data-aos-delay="1000">
                    <div class="card mb-20 active">
                        <div class="card-header tab-shadow" id="headingOne">
                            <h3 class="mb-0"><button class="btn btn-link btn-block text-left" type="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapseOne" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="collapseOne"> Owner</button> </h3>
                        </div>
                        <div id="collapseOne" class="collapse show" aria-labelledby="headingOne" data-parent="#accordionExample">
                            <div class="card-body"> I interviewed a small business owner several times via online tools to understand the background, her expectations, frustrations, and desired outcomes. </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card mb-20">
                        <div class="card-header tab-shadow" id="headingTwo">
                            <h3 class="mb-0"><button class="btn btn-link btn-block text-left collapsed" type="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapseTwo" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseTwo"> End users</button> </h3>
                        </div>
                        <div id="collapseTwo" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="headingTwo" data-parent="#accordionExample">
                            <div class="card-body"> I walked into establishments where I felt comfortable to interview potential users. In addition to interviews, I used survey questions and sample product testing. I was pretty successful in finding out about their various backgrounds,
                                personal shopping habits, frustrations with the technology, and their desired outcomes when it comes to interactions with customer services. </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card mb-20">
                        <div class="card-header tab-shadow" id="headingThree">
                            <h3 class="mb-0"><button class="btn btn-link btn-block text-left collapsed" type="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapseThree" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseThree"> Online community</button> </h3>
                        </div>
                        <div id="collapseThree" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="headingThree" data-parent="#accordionExample">
                            <div class="card-body"> I also reached out to online scented candle lovers community - community forums and bloggers. They were happy to share about their preferences, expectations, and frustrations. They even volunteered to test the scented candles.
                                I reached out to meditation practitioners too. According to them, they use candles to help with focus during meditation. For this purpose, any candle can be used, so I didn’t persist in finding out more when it comes to
                                this population. </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card mb-20">
                        <div class="card-header tab-shadow" id="headingFour">
                            <h3 class="mb-0"><button class="btn btn-link btn-block text-left collapsed" type="button" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#collapseFour" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseFour"> Observations</button> </h3>
                        </div>
                        <div id="collapseFour" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="headingFour" data-parent="#accordionExample">
                            <div class="card-body"> I observed some users to understand how they go about searching for products online, how they decide to land on certain e-commerce shops, and how they shop on mobile and other devices. It was curious that all users I encountered
                                pretty much expected shops to adhere to already established e-commerce design patterns. They were frustrated with deviations. It seems that users pretty much caught up with the user experience guidelines, while businesses
                                still offer poor user experiences to them. </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
