                <div class="persona-content col-lg-6 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12">
                    <h6 class="text-boja">SHOPPING</h6>
                    <h4 class="text-boja">Decision making</h4>
                    <p>When shopping, he first checks the nearby stores on his mobile phone to see if the product he needs is available. If he finds the right product nearby, he goes to the store to purchase the product. </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row no-gutters align-items-center d-flex justify-content-between" data-aos="zoom-in" data-aos-duration="3000" data-aos-easing="ease-in-out-cubic">
                <div class="persona-content col-lg-6 col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12">
                    <h6 class="text-boja">PSYCHOLOGY</h6>
                    <h4 class="text-boja">Can't wait</h4>
                    <p>Most of the time, he gets frustrated because he can’t find what he needs online. And when he finds what he needs, he gets frustrated in store because of the long checkout lines. And he hates it when someone tries to cut in line in
                        front of him.
                        <p>
                            <p>“Over my dead body,” he said. “I have to intervene to remind them of their place in line. I just have to.” </p>
                </div>
