    <section class="section wireframe-bg mt-150" id="ecommerce_wireframes">
        <div class="container-fluid">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="card-deck justify-content-around">
                    <div class="col-xl-4 col-lg-8 col-md-8 col-sm-12 pt-3 box-shadow" data-aos="zoom-in" data-aos-duration="2000" data-aos-easing="ease-in-out-cubic">
                        <div class="card">
                            <div class="card-body">
                                <h4 class="card-title mt-20">Wireframes</h4>
                                <p class="card-text">We stayed for a long time in this phase because it took a long time to collect the final text copy. I had to have the text ready before going to the prototype stage.</p>
                                <p class="card-text">Then I came up with the final layout, navigation and user flows depending on the type of user that would visit the e-commerce store.</p>
                                <p> Wireframing was done directly with Shopify Liquid on the Shopify platform.</p>
                                <p class="card-text"> This is the wireframe example.</p><a href="https://gew7f68xdvf33bhv-26537820218.shopifypreview.com" target="_blank" class="btn btn-primary">Take a look</a> </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-xl-4 col-lg-8 col-md-8 col-sm-12 pt-3 mt-50 box-shadow jobs-cont" id="ecommerce_prototypes" data-aos="zoom-in" data-aos-duration="2000" data-aos-easing="ease-in-out-cubic" data-aos-delay="1000">
                        <div class="card">
                            <div class="card-body">
                                <h4 class="card-title">Prototypes</h4>
                                <p class="card-text">I collected and edited photo assets, implemented brand colors and incorporated style guide components.</p>
                                <p class="card-text">Everything on the Web site was done from scratch, although we expected that Shopify would take care of the shopping and inventory capacity. That included creating the shopping cart because it didn’t work on mobile devices;
                                    creating the search functionality because the Shopify template didn’t show results correctly; creating the product pages, etc. </p>
                                <p>This is the prototype example.</p><a href="https://dw1vs8l2rkc3iqvk-26537820218.shopifypreview.com" target="_blank" class="btn btn-primary mb-20">Take a look</a> </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row justify-content-around mt-100" id="ecommerce_final">
                <div class="col-xl-5 col-md-6 col-sm-12 pt-3 box-shadow jobs-cont" data-aos="zoom-in" data-aos-duration="2000" data-aos-easing="ease-in-out-cubic">
                    <div class="card">
                        <div class="card-body">
                            <h4 class="card-title">Final version</h4>
                            <p class="card-text">We tested all the functionalities, especially shopping with a variety of payment methods. We tested all possible user shopping flows.</p>
                            <p class="card-text">I implemented the SEO, page optimization, published the Web site, and handed over the user guide.</p><a href="https://tanjadesign.myshopify.com/" target="_blank" class="btn btn-primary mb-20">Enjoy</a> </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
